Added a diagnostic mode to ButtonServerCasters that automatically runs when pygame or GPIO boards are not detected. In this diagnostic mode the user can send the OSC messages by simulating GPI button presses or releases. The sendondetect() function has been moved to x32-broadcast because it has been substantially changed and the diagnostic mode may be good to be added to the ProducerServer and the PanelServer

Added protection against wrong bus numbers. When the server is starting it will throw an error when someone selects bus numbers that are not in the range of 1-16. Furthermore the buttons now ignore double bus numbers (i.e. if there is only a single caster bus rather than 2, pressing the 'talk to both casters' button will still only talk to a single bus). This feauture prevents bus numbers adding up to completely different talk2 destmaps, which could cause the intercom to be sent to stream or PA.

DCA Generation
All DCA's and subsequent channels in their groups are now automatically added to the message handlers. At this stage only editing of the dictionary is necessary. Also added some error handling for imports

CSV Reading
Added a x32CSGO.csv file which is read from to generate the ChannelDict variable rather than defining it inside the server script.

DCA Fixed
